,"axes[0,0].set_ylabel(\"3PA / FGA\")\n","axes[0,0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n","\n","# Pace\n","pace = team_stats.groupby(\"SEASON\")[\"E_PACE\"].mean().reindex(season_order)\n","axes[0,1].plot(pace.index, pace.values, marker=\"o\", color=\"#c8102e\", linewidth=2)\n","axes[0,1].set_title(\"Avg League Pace\")\n","axes[0,1].set_ylabel(\"Possessions per 48 min\")\n","axes[0,1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n","\n","# Net rating spread\n","net_spread = team_stats.groupby(\"SEASON\")[\"E_NET_RATING\"].std().reindex(season_order)\n","axes[1,0].plot(net_spread.index, net_spread.values, marker=\"o\", color=\"#007a33\", linewidth=2)\n","axes[1,0].set_title(\"Net Rating Spread (Std Dev)\\nHigher = More Competitive Imbalance\")\n","axes[1,0].set_ylabel(\"Std Dev of Net Rating\")\n","axes[1,0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n","\n","# True Shooting %\n","ts = players.groupby(\"SEASON\")[\"TS_PCT\"].mean().reindex(season_order)\n","axes[1,1].plot(ts.index, ts.values, marker=\"o\", color=\"#f58220\", linewidth=2)\n","axes[1,1].set_title(\"Avg True Shooting %\")\n","axes[1,1].set_ylabel(\"TS%\")\n","axes[1,1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.savefig(\"league_trends.png\", dpi=150)\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":693},"id":"2RWpJpFGrG5Z","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1775701936866,"user_tz":420,"elapsed":951,"user":{"displayName":"Faisal Alessa","userId":"15182016480962682188"}},"outputId":"0a5bc7fa-0d5a-4c8f-ccce-c4d5f137f217"},"execution_count":33,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1400x1000 with 4 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Summary of Key Findings\n","\n","This preliminary analysis establishes a strong foundation for the data warehouse and Tableau dashboard phases of the project. Across four seasons of NBA data, several clear patterns emerge that directly inform front office decision-making.\n","\n","Net Rating is the single most reliable predictor of team success, explaining the large majority of variance in win percentage. This validates our decision to center the warehouse around efficiency ratings rather than raw counting stats. On offense, Effective FG% and assist rate are the strongest positive correlates with winning, while turnover rate is the most damaging metric — suggesting that teams should prioritize shot quality and ball security above all else.\n","\n","At the player level, no single metric tells the full story. The composite efficiency score combining Net Rating, True Shooting %, PIE, and Plus/Minus surfaces the most impactful players across all positions more reliably than any individual statistic. The playoff analysis reveals meaningful variance in how players perform under postseason pressure, which is a critical input for roster construction decisions. Finally, hustle stats identify a category of role players who contribute significantly beyond the box score and are likely undervalued on the open market.\n","\n","The next phase of the project will load all of this data into a structured relational database, enforce schema constraints and surrogate keys, and connect the warehouse to Tableau for interactive dashboard development."],"metadata":{"id":"hGiDlHdVrIkY"}}]}